<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-gGVKbtkdF9-NZ8B4iv5H6Q" name=",_7GR_EL-eEd2e1-cAeXIm5A" guid="-gGVKbtkdF9-NZ8B4iv5H6Q" changeDate="2008-12-01T12:55:38.571+0100">
  <mainDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>The result of this task is the complete service composition specification expressed as a UML diagram, which will be very similar to that obtained in the previous task. UML notes can be used to include information about the non functional requirements in the composition design diagram. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>Note: Once again, experience is very important. If possible, try to have in mind own developed services to define the composition and the impact of non functional requirements on it.&lt;/SPAN></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBUgUMHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Gather all non functional requirements to be fulfilled by the composition " guid="_UBUgUMHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>First, extract all non functional requirements. Good sources of non functional requirements are “System Requirements”, SSM and dependencies. If the company has experience, it is a good idea to reuse all the knowledge to identify new requirements. Enterprise policies might add new non functional requirements to achieve some QoS levels. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: ES-TRAD; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>Do not forget that not all the requirements are written, so it is important to pay attention to some non functional requirements which can be deducted due to transactions or security issues, for example. &lt;/SPAN></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBUgUsHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Analyse how each non functional requirement affects to the composition " guid="_UBUgUsHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>The next step is to analyse the impact of each non functional requirement. Identify the functional parts affected by each non functional requirement and determine if those requirements can be fulfilled following the actual design of the composition. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Once this step is finished, developers will be able to determine which parts of the composition will have to be modified to fulfil all the requirements. Previous experience will be very helpful to identify those parts usually affected by the same non functional requirements. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBUgUcHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Complete composition design in such a way it fulfils non functional requirements  " guid="_UBUgUcHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>To finish this task, make necessary changes to fulfil non functional requirements in those parts of the composition which were identified in the previous step. At this point, the composition will be also completed defining security aspects, transactions within the composition and QoS levels to be achieved. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Have in mind that, since error handling, security and transactions will add information to the actual composition, QoS aspects might require important changes due to the way some tasks have to be done and the services to be used (perform redundant tasks, change services requirements, add intermediary tasks for language or payment issues…). &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;span&#xD;
style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>The&#xD;
business process is completed with information about non functional requirements necessary to guarantee the good execution&#xD;
of the composition and to fulfil user expectations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span>&lt;/span></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
